  "body": "There is no need to keep all the trie logs for a near-head node as the state for old blocks is rarely needed. This will place a configurable limit on how many trie logs are kept reducing storage needed for a node.\r\n\r\n* Add configurable limit for number trie logs to be kept. This should be the same as the Bonsai read limit config \r\n--bonsai-maximum-back-layers-to-load parameter\r\n* Prune old trie logs that are not needed\r\n* Trie logs are stored by block hash so there will need to be a way of determining with block hashes to remove the trie logs for\r\n* The logic used for the block pruning which keeps a list of block hashes for each block number could possibly be reused for pruning the trie log\r\n* This should be enabled independently of the chain data pruning feature and can be used together\r\n* Measure storage saved by having the trie log pruning enabled\r\n* Test that reorgs have their trie log pruned\r\n\r\nAcceptance Criteria\r\n* DB size of long running node should be the same before and after resync\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\n* The `ChainDataPruner` could be a helpful place to start and reuse some of the same logic\r\n\r\nTasks:\r\n- [x] First iteration of `--Xbonsai-trie-log-pruning-enabled`: https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/pull/6026 \r\n- [x] Consider using safeBlock instead of 512 layers to retain\r\n  - would be a nice strategy to prune only blocks older than RETAINED_LAYERS that have a subsequent finalized blockhash\r\n- [x] Consider belts and braces protection during rollback/forward in case pruned trielog may be in use\r\n  - not sure how useful this is now we only prune finalized blocks\r\n- [ ] DB size of long running node should be the same before and after resync - \r\n  - [x]  without flat db https://gist.github.com/siladu/0a6fe37fe6de350cef233136e237a6e4\r\n  - [ ] with flat db - underway with `simon-flatdb*`\r\n- [ ] Measure storage saved by having the trie log pruning enabled - underway on `*simon-6026*` and `*simon-flatdb*` nodes\r\n     ```\r\n       crontab -e \r\n       \r\n       0 16 * * * echo \"\\n\\n=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=\\n$(date)\\n\" >> /home/simon.dudley/rocksdb-usage.txt 2>&1\r\n       1 16 * * * time /opt/besu/6000/bin/besu --config-file=/etc/besu/config.toml operator x-rocksdb usage >> /home/simon.dudley/rocksdb-usage.txt 2>&1\r\n     ```\r\n   - 2 week old TRIE_LOG_STORAGE saving is 6GB = 3GB per week\r\n   - 7 week old TRIE_LOG_STORAGE saving is 22GB = 3.14GB per week\r\n- [x] Subcommand to one-off prune the backlog, see https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/pull/6000\r\n  - [x] RocksDB usage subcommand - https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/pull/6185\r\n  - [x] Subcommand to prune trie-logs \"offline\" - ~~https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/pull/6188 (needs testing on an old node to see how long it might take to run)~~  https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/pull/6303\r\n\r\n- [ ] Reorg acceptance test\r\n  - [ ] Convert this script to AT: https://gist.github.com/siladu/bde571af9880733d4dfdee9f30ce0fc4\r\n- [ ] Reuse `--bonsai-historical-block-limit` instead of `--Xbonsai-trie-log-retention-threshold`\r\n  - These two options are incompatible due to retention-threshold having a *minimum* value of 512, so we need to remove the minimum value constraint from the pruning logic.\r\n- [ ] Rename `--Xbonsai-trie-log-pruning-enabled` to `--Xbonsai-limit-trie-logs-enabled` - YES\r\n- [ ] Prevent block building from saving orphaned trie logs ?\r\n- [ ] Consider an option to only prune forks\r\n- [ ] Optimisation 1: Move pruning to async thread\r\n  - https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/pull/6026#issuecomment-1814774736\r\n- [ ] Optimisation 2: Prune in batches instead of every block?\r\n- [ ] Optimisation 3: Cache finalizedBlockHeader in Blockchain or use Observer pattern to pass it to the pruner",
